caption: Hope you can see this espectacle when you visit this place. It's amazing to see the fountain working. During my visit it only lasted for a couple of minutes, but it was really nice  In summer this place is crowded with people, so be sure to check before going. But still, you'll love it.

Trocadero Fountain The Warsaw Fountain is located in the Trocadero Gardens, below the Trocadero Palace, in the 6th arrondissement.  The main feature, called the Warsaw Fountain, is a 12-meter-tall basin; and ten arches of water. At one end, facing the Seine, are 20 powerful water cannons, capable of shooting a jet of water 50 meters away. Above the long basin are two smaller ones, linked to the lower basin by cascades flanked by 32-meter-high water sprays. These fountains are the only gallery fountains still standing today, and they still function the same. In 2011, the fountain's waterworks were completely renovated and a modern pumping system was installed.

We came by on New Years Day and the fountain wasn't on. We came to the Trocadero Esplanade area to get a nice view of the Eiffel Tower, which was covered by fog. The fountain is located below the esplanade. It wasn't on but the size of it was incredible. I would imagine that it would be really impressive if the whole thing was running. It was still worth a look even though it wasn't running.
